                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.11T54/205.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs, after an interview with the President, said
                    to-day to Mr. Schuyler that he would soon send me a note refusing arbitration,
                    not only because arbitration is impracticable on the basis of the protocol, but
                    because the Government and the Company were expecting to arrange an amicable
                    settlement, the terms of which will be submitted to the Department which, he
                    said, had agreed to be judge of its justice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
